<Author>letmbkids
<Content>Hotel Domus grew on us Our initial impression was disappointing but over the two days we stayed here it grew on us. The only other people we saw staying here were old men which was kinda weird but once we got accustomed to our surroundings, it was okay. I'm not sure I would stay here again. We seriously overpaid because we were there for World Cup. Our next visit to Berlin, we'll stay near Potsdamer Platz.Rooms were fair, carpet of Days Inn quality, bathrooms tiny. You could smell smoke from adjoining rooms during the night. We never even tried the breakfast but opted for the fresh fruit market next door. The front desk staff was friendly and accomodating.One highlight was the Hamlet restaurant nearby. Great atmosphere, friendly service and good food. 
